		2.3.2 Cannot enable Phone Services	
Refreshed to a Mac for the first time, following the instructions for setting up Jabber. I already went through eStore to request phone and video services, and received a confirmation email that the request is complete. Under Jabber-->Preferences-->Accounts Voicemail has the nice green checkmark, but Phone Services continues to have the dreaded red X, and it keeps telling me "invalid credentials". I assume under "User Settings" I'm supposed to put my CEC username and password, right? So what could be wrong?
 
Thanks,
 
-- Jamal
 
Responses
David Cosca

Hi Jamal,

Some questions:

What version of Jabber Mac did you download?

Have you used the calling/phone feature on your Mac before?

Could you try syncing your CEC username and password in phone.cisco.com?

 

Also, could you send me a screenshot of your phone account options with server info/error message?

Thanks,

David

